1. Create a Java project in your editor of choice.

2. Using Rest Assured make a POST request to https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking/1 that fails to create a new booking.

3. Using Rest Assured make a POST request to https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking/1 that creates a new booking.

3.1. Validate that the response contains the same values in the tags that were provided as part of the POST

3.2. Validate that the response status code is as expected

4. From the response get the id of new booking and use it for a GET request to  https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/booking/id

4.1. Validate that the response contains the same values in the tags that were provided as part of the POST

4.2. Validate that the response status code is as expected

5. From the response save the "firstname" and "lastname" values to a new variable called "fullName"

6. Using Selenium Webdriver open  https://restful-booker.herokuapp.com/apidoc/index.html

7. In the upper left corner there is a "Filter" textbox, input the value of the "fullName" variable in that textbox.

8. If the text "restful-booker" is present on the page then print out "Text Found", else print out "Text Not Found"
